<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910912-0049</DOCNO><DOCID>910912-0049.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Boole andamp; Babbage Inc.:   About 10% of Work Force   Is Fired to Reduce Costs</HL><DATE>09/12/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5</SO><CO>   BOOL</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>SOFTWARE (SOF)</IN><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Boole andamp; Babbage Inc. said it fired 75 employees, or about10% of the software concern's work force, to help containcosts.   The Sunnyvale, Calif., company, which has lost $3.6million during the first three quarters of its fiscal yearending Sept. 30, said it will take a one-time charge of $1.5million against fourth-quarter operating earnings forseverance costs and other expenses associated with a costreduction plan. The firings brought Boole andamp; Babbage's totalheadcount down to 640, a level the company said should be lowenough to increase profitability.</LP><TEXT>   Boole andamp; Babbage also said fiscal 1991 revenue would bereduced by up to $1.5 million due to a changed accountingprocedure. The company said this wouldn't affect its cashflow or cash balance.</TEXT></DOC>